commit.message:
Make sure we load table data after start up.

Table previously uses a lazy load mechanism. This would make the initial
toggle being slow. This has been an issue on certain platform because
it's introducing a noticable sutter.

Unlikely pinyin, we need to load data based on the input method group,
so we need to defer until the input method manager is ready.

commit.message:
Fix punctuation state cancelling

When adding support for punctuation candidate, we introduced a bug that
punctuation state is not cleared correctly.

pushPunctuation should always be called regardless we need punctuation
candidates.

Fix #156
